      <title>Childcare and the Kita System: Turkey vs Germany</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/germany/living/kita-childcare-turkey-vs-germany/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/germany/living/kita-childcare-turkey-vs-germany/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Childcare &amp;amp; the Kita System: Turkey vs Germany&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;childcare--the-kita-system-turkey-vs-germany&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#childcare--the-kita-system-turkey-vs-germany&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Finding a Kita spot in Munich is harder than finding a flat. But the system, when you&amp;rsquo;re in it, is remarkable.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;🇹🇷 Turkey: Family First, State Second&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;-turkey-family-first-state-second&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#-turkey-family-first-state-second&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In Turkey, childcare is predominantly family-based. Grandparents — especially grandmothers — play a central role in raising young children. This is cultural expectation as much as practical arrangement.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
